post_text: The Bedford Fall Foliage Festival Committee must announce, with deep regret, that we are cancelling the 2020 Bedford Fall Foliage Festival. We were planning to wait until Labor Day to make our decision, however, with the state of the virus at this time, we do not believe that Governor Wolf will relax the mandated limit of 250 people at an outdoor event. This mandate makes it impossible for us to receive Penn DOT approval to close the streets. We regret the added hardship this decision makes for our vendors and shoppers, but be assured that we are already in planning for the 2021 festival.
shared_text:
Bedford's Fall Foliage Festival is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
August 3 at 8:54 PM ¬∑

The Bedford Fall Foliage Festival Committee must announce, with deep regret, that we are cancelling the 2020 Bedford Fall Foliage Festival. We were planning to wait until Labor Day to make our decision, however, with the state of the virus at this time, we do not believe that Governor Wolf will relax the mandated limit of 250 people at an outdoor event. This mandate makes it impossible for us to receive Penn DOT approval to close the streets. We regret the added hardship this decision makes for our vendors and shoppers, but be assured that we are already in planning for the 2021 festival.
text:
The Bedford Fall Foliage Festival Committee must announce, with deep regret, that we are cancelling the 2020 Bedford Fall Foliage Festival. We were planning to wait until Labor Day to make our decision, however, with the state of the virus at this time, we do not believe that Governor Wolf will relax the mandated limit of 250 people at an outdoor event. This mandate makes it impossible for us to receive Penn DOT approval to close the streets. We regret the added hardship this decision makes for our vendors and shoppers, but be assured that we are already in planning for the 2021 festival.

Bedford's Fall Foliage Festival is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
August 3 at 8:54 PM ¬∑

The Bedford Fall Foliage Festival Committee must announce, with deep regret, that we are cancelling the 2020 Bedford Fall Foliage Festival. We were planning to wait until Labor Day to make our decision, however, with the state of the virus at this time, we do not believe that Governor Wolf will relax the mandated limit of 250 people at an outdoor event. This mandate makes it impossible for us to receive Penn DOT approval to close the streets. We regret the added hardship this decision makes for our vendors and shoppers, but be assured that we are already in planning for the 2021 festival.

For $149 we will not only update your computer to Windows 10 but also upgrade your system with by cloning your hard drive to a new 120GB solid-state drive (a $99 value). These lightning-fast drives will help extend the life of your computer as you move into the new decade.

If you are interested in taking advantage of this special, please contact our office at 814-799-0274 or visit Cyber Protection Group at 2230 Woodbury Pike, Suite 1, Loysburg. Valid on computers with compatible size drives, upgrades are available.

The US National Weather Service State College PA has issued a special weather advisory for our area.

EXPECT WIDESPREAD FOG AND PATCHES OF DENSE FOG

A widespread fog is locally dense, especially on the ridge tops. Visibilities are generally just one quarter to one half of a mile, but could be only a few hundred feet in places.

Please slow down and use only low-beam headlights if you are traveling this morning. Allow plenty of extra time to reach your
destination.

* WHAT...Light freezing rain expected. Total ice accumulations of a light glaze, mainly on the ridgetops.

* WHERE...Portions of central Pennsylvania.(see below for complete list)

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 2 PM EST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Untreated sidewalks, roads and bridges could be slippery. The threat of icy roads should end by early afternoon, as temperatures rise into the mid 30s.

Northern Lycoming-Southern Clinton-Union-Snyder- Including the cities of Renovo, Philipsburg, State College, Johnstown, Altoona, Huntingdon, Mount Union, Lewistown, Mifflintown, Somerset, Bedford, McConnellsburg, Chambersburg,
Trout Run, Lock Haven, Lewisburg, and Selinsgrove

Weather announcement by the US National Weather Service State College PA.

...Wintry mix at higher elevations this evening into tonight...

Areas of freezing rain may bring a light glaze of ice across the higher elevations this evening into tonight.

The icy mix will likely transition to a period of light snow late tonight into the predawn hours Sunday, with accumulations up to 1 inch possible.

Ice and snow accumulation will primarily be confined to the higher terrain north and west of Interstate 99.

Be alert for slick spots on untreated roads and elevated surfaces.

**Updated** Mother and children were found. The father in-law, Edgar Lee Decker Jr., is in custody. No other details are known at this time. **

- Missing Bedford County Family -
Alicia Helsel Brumbaugh and her two children are reported missing and endangered. They were last seen with her father in-law, who has an active felony warrant in Blair County. They maybe traveling in a black 2005 Chevrolet Avalanche - licence number ZGZ-6781. Please contact the police with any details of their location.
shared_text:
National Center For Missing and Endangered, Inc.
November 12, 2019 at 8:21 AM ¬∑

***UPDATE- 11/12/2019
The missing and endangered Mother and children from Pennsylvania have been located. State police said they have located a 31-year-old mother and her two young children who were previously missing and considered endangered.

Police said they stopped a vehicle they were looking for along State Route 422 at Oakland Avenue in White Township, Indiana County.

#Pennsylvania #IndianaCounty #ABC #CBS #NBC #Fox

post_text: It was brought to our attention that there has been a mistake on the ballots for tomorrow's election for Bedford County. Mike Miller and Steve Cottle are registered Republican candidates, but have been listed as Democratic candidates. After one of the candidates contacted the courthouse, it was confirmed a mistake.
shared_text:
Mike Miller
November 4, 2019 at 2:13 PM ¬∑

It was brought to my attention that there has been a mistake on the ballots for tomorrow's election. I am a registered republican candidate, but myself as well as another republican (Steve Cottle) have been listed as democrat. I want to make sure it is clear that I am a registered republican. After talking to the courthouse, it was a confirmed mistake. I thank all of you for your support. Please feel free to share this out so people are aware. You will not be able to vote for us if you vote straight republican. You will have to select us.

Last night, we had the privilege of visiting one of the best decorated homes for Halloween in Roaring Spring. This display took Mike Sr. and Amy Kurtz over a month to create.

At first, you‚Äôll see the house lined with lights, but the closer to the house is when you see the detail and time put into their display. Many creatures are lurking in their yard, along with ghostly visitors in windows, and a headless horseman. Weather permitting, this display will be visible on Burkettown Road until October 31st.

If you enjoy their Halloween house, make sure you come back for Christmas display‚Ä¶ you might even see Santa!

post_text:
Do you know what these 3 silver pieces have in common?

They all play a key part in the history of our region. Shown below are the South Fork Dam/Johnstown Flood of 1889, the Pennsylvania K-4 Locomotive/Horseshoe Curve, and Pennsylvania State University. In addition, to preserving a time or place in our community, these art bullion bars also hold investment value. They are one-ounce silver bars with artwork engraved on both sides and were produced to commemorate an important historical event or display cultural significance. Not only are they a valuable addition to any collector, but they also make great gifts! If you were to receive one of these historical pieces, which would you pick?

On Friday, October 4th, Keystone Coin & Bullion will be giving away one of these bullion bars randomly to one of our followers. In order to qualify, you must tell us below which one is your favorite? Also, you must subscribe to Keystone Coin & Bullion. If you are interested in learning more about bullions and coins, please contact Matt Snyder.

Special Weather Statement
National Weather Service State College PA
745 PM EDT Sat Sep 28 2019

PAZ024-025-033-034-290045-
Bedford PA-Somerset PA-Blair PA-Cambria PA-
745 PM EDT Sat Sep 28 2019

...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL AFFECT PARTS OF BEDFORD...SOMERSET...
BLAIR...AND CAMBRIA COUNTIES UNTIL 845 PM EDT...

At 745 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated a line of showers and
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Vinco to 7 miles
north of Seven Springs. Movement was east at 25 mph.

Wind gusts to 40 mph and pea size hail are possible.

Locations impacted include...
Johnstown, Somerset, Westmont, Windber, Belmont, Portage, Geistown,
Southmont, Friedens, Vinco, Boswell, Dale, East Conemaugh,
Salix-Beauty Line Park, Davidsville, Central City,
Beaverdale-Lloydell, Paint, Jerome and South Fork.
